      "writtenOn": "2010-11-17T20:52:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You want to only keep the ready bits corresponding to what is wanted, so it\u0027s a AND operation.\n\nI.e. let\u0027s say that READY \u003d\u003d READ+WRITE, so the LoopIo is pending and its callback hasn\u0027t been called yet.\n\nThis function is called by another callback, which decides that it wants to disable READ for this LoopIo (for some reason), so you will have WANTED \u003d\u003d READ\n\nYou don\u0027t want to keep the WRITE bit in READY then.",
      "parentUuid": "AAAA9n///1w\u003d",
